          <lg n="1">
            <l xml:id="swift-334-174F-line-1" n="1">When Foes are o'ercome We preserve them from Slaughter,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-334-174F-line-2" n="2">To be Hewers of <hi rend="large-writing-underlined">Wood<hi rend="italics"/> and Drawers of Water;</hi></l>
            <l xml:id="swift-334-174F-line-3" n="3">Now altho' to draw water is not very good,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-334-174F-line-4" n="4">Yet We all should rejoyce to be Hewers of <hi rend="large-writing-underlined">Wood</hi>.</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-334-174F-line-5" n="5">I own it hath often provokd me to mutter,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-334-174F-line-6" n="6">That a rogue so obscure should make such a Clutter:</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-334-174F-line-7" n="7">But ancient Philosophers wisely remark,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-334-174F-line-8" n="8">That old rotten <hi rend="large-writing-underlined">Wood</hi> will shine in the dark.</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-334-174F-line-9" n="9">The Heathens we read had Gods made of Wood,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-334-174F-line-10" n="10">Who could do 'em no harm, if they did 'em no good,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-334-174F-line-11" n="11">But this Idol <hi rend="large-writing">Wood</hi> may do Us great evill,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-334-174F-line-12" n="12">Their Gods were of <hi rend="large-writing">Wood</hi>, but our Wood is the Devill.</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-334-174F-line-13" n="13">To cutt down fine <hi rend="large-writing">Wood</hi> is a very bad thing,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-334-174F-line-14" n="14">And yet We all know much Gold it will bring,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-334-174F-line-15" n="15">Then if cutting down <hi rend="large-writing">Wood</hi> brings money good store,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-334-174F-line-16" n="16">Our money to keep lett us Cutt down one more.</l>
            <l rend="indent(1)" xml:id="swift-334-174F-line-17" n="17">Now hear an old Tale: There anciently stood</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-334-174F-line-18" n="18">(I forgett in what Church) an Image of Wood,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-334-174F-line-19" n="19">Concerning this Image there went a prediction,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-334-174F-line-20" n="20">It would burn a whole Forrest; nor was it a Fiction,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-334-174F-line-21" n="21">'Twas cutt into faggots, and putt to the flame,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-334-174F-line-22" n="22">To burn an old Fryar One Forrest by name,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-334-174F-line-23" n="23">My Tale is a wise one, if well understood,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-334-174F-line-24" n="24">Find You but the Fryar, and I'le find the <hi rend="large-writing">Wood</hi>.</l>
            <l rend="indent(1)" xml:id="swift-334-174F-line-25" n="25">I hear among schollars there is a great doubt,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-334-174F-line-26" n="26">From what kind of tree this <hi rend="large-writing">Wood</hi> was hewn out;</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-334-174F-line-27" n="27">Teague made a good pun, by a brogue in his speech,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-334-174F-line-28" n="28">And said, By my shoul he's the Son of a <hi rend="large-writing">Beech</hi>;</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-334-174F-line-29" n="29">Some call him a <hi rend="large-writing">Thorn</hi>, the curse of a Nation,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-334-174F-line-30" n="30">As thorns were designd to be from the Creation;</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-334-174F-line-31" n="31">Some think him cutt out from the poisonous Yew,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-334-174F-line-32" n="32">Beneath whose ill shade no plant ever grew;</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-334-174F-line-33" n="33">Some say he's a <hi rend="large-writing">Birch</hi>, a thought very odd,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-334-174F-line-34" n="34">For none but a Dunce would come under his Rod:</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-334-174F-line-35" n="35">But I'll tell you the Secret, &amp; pray do not blab,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-334-174F-line-36" n="36">He is an old Stump cutt out of a <hi rend="italics">Crab</hi>,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-334-174F-line-37" n="37">And England has putt this Crab to a hard use,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-334-174F-line-38" n="38">To cudgell Our bones, &amp; for drink give us Verjuice;</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-334-174F-line-39" n="39">And therefore his <hi rend="large-writing">Witnesses</hi> justly may boast,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-334-174F-line-40" n="40">That none are more properly Knights of the Post.</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-334-174F-line-41" n="41">om.</l>
