            <l rend="indent(1)" xml:id="swift-334-174F-line-69" n="69">I ne're could indure my Talent to Smother,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-334-174F-line-70" n="70">I told you one Tale, I'le tell you another;</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-334-174F-line-71" n="71">A Joyner, to fasten a Saint in a nitch,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-334-174F-line-72" n="72">Bor'd a large Augerhole in the Images breech,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-334-174F-line-73" n="73">But finding the Statue to make no complaint,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-334-174F-line-74" n="74">He would ne'er be convinc'd it was a true Saint:</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-334-174F-line-75" n="75">When the true <hi rend="large-writing">Wood</hi> arrives, as he soon will no doubt,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-334-174F-line-76" n="76">(For thats but a <note place="foot">·Woods Effigies was carryd about &amp; burnt.</note> Sham <hi rend="large-writing">Wood</hi> they carry about)</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-334-174F-line-77" n="77">What Stuff he is made on you quickly may find,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-334-174F-line-78" n="78">If you make the same tryal, and bore him behind,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-334-174F-line-79" n="79">I'll hold you a groat, when you wimble his bum</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-334-174F-line-80" n="80">He'l bellow as loud as the De'il in a drum.</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-334-174F-line-81" n="81">From me I declare you shall have no denyal,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-334-174F-line-82" n="82">For there can be no harm in making a Tryal,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-334-174F-line-83" n="83">And when to the joy of Your hearts he has roar'd,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-334-174F-line-84" n="84">You may shew him about for a new <hi rend="large-writing">Groaning Board</hi>.</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-334-174F-line-85" n="85">om.</l>
