            <l xml:id="swift-334-174F-line-108" n="108">om.</l>
            <l rend="indent(1)" xml:id="swift-334-174F-line-109" n="109">Hear one Story more; and then I will stop,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-334-174F-line-110" n="110">I dream't, <hi rend="large-writing">Wood</hi> was told he should dye by a Drop,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-334-174F-line-111" n="111">So methought he resolv'd no liquor to taste,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-334-174F-line-112" n="112">For fear the first Drop might as well be his last;</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-334-174F-line-113" n="113">But dreams are like Oracles, 'its hard to explain 'em,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-334-174F-line-114" n="114">For it provd that he dy'd by a Drop at Kilmainham;<note place="foot">·Their Tyburn or place of Execution.</note></l>
            <l xml:id="swift-334-174F-line-115" n="115">I wakd' w<hi rend="superscript">tḥ</hi> delight, and not without hope,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-334-174F-line-116" n="116">Very soon to see <hi rend="large-writing">Wood</hi> drop down from a Rope.</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-334-174F-line-117" n="117">How he, and how We at each other should grin!</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-334-174F-line-118" n="118">Tis kindness to hold a Friend up by the Chin.</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-334-174F-line-119" n="119">But soft, says the Herald, I cannot agree,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-334-174F-line-120" n="120">For Metall on Metall is false Heraldry,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-334-174F-line-121" n="121">Why that may be true, yet <hi rend="large-writing">Wood</hi> upon <hi rend="large-writing">Wood</hi></l>
            <l xml:id="swift-334-174F-line-122" n="122">Ile maintain w<hi rend="superscript">tḥ</hi> my Life is Heraldry good.</l>
          </lg>
